==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sinistrous
<hw>Sin"is*trous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Sinister</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Being on the left side;
inclined to the left; sinistral.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Sinistrous</xex>
gravity.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1345 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Wrong; absurd; perverse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A knave or fool can do no harm, even by the most
<qex>sinistrous</qex> and absurd choice.</q>
<rj><qau>Bentley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinistrously</ent>⟦br⟧
